{
  "stem": "7739.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Howard Chandler.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My original name was Hy Wajchendler.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was born and raised in a small town in central Poland in the province of Kielce by the name of Wierzbnik,Wie now known as Starachowice.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in 1928, December 5, 1928.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a small town, relatively speaking.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It had big ammunition factories in those days even before the war, long before the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Jewish population, I would-- I would imagine was around 3,000 people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The general population must have been around 20,000 people, and they were more or less scattered in the outlying areas of town, because the center of the town was mostly occupied mostly by Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, there were Gentile people there, as well, but mostly around the market square, where business took place.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a market there on Thursdays and the peasants and the farmers of the surrounding area used to bring their produce and their fruit and it was a-- and merchants used to come display their wares.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was quite a day to look forward to.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father had a store and he also had a spot in the marketplace, where we would go on Thursday.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He would take our ware out there, display them in this designated square-- and he used to sell kitchenware there, pots, pans, glasses, china, things like this.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "On Wednesday night, we packed the wagon, which I was a helper, as well, as well as the other children.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this was Thursday.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Jewish population there, I guess, as they were throughout Poland, mostly religious people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were observant Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Sabbath was kept strictly, so were the other holidays, of course.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
